english:
  title: The Difficulty of the Road
  author: Lee Sung-in
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Difficult, so difficult is the road ahead.
    If I cry out once, will you turn to look at me once?
    Even the smooth paths of peacetime are choked with thorns,
    And in the bright daylight of the great city, wolves and tigers prowl.
    A thousand worries burn my breast, my entrails crumble,
    Yet hearing the rooster's call, I cannot help but dance at midnight.
    When dawn breaks and I step through the door, where can I go?
    Water overturns the boat, mountains shatter the cart.
    Have you not seen the wealthy sons of Chang'an's streets,
    Who lived their whole lives without reading a single book?
  footnotes:
    - Chang'an refers to the ancient capital, here symbolizing the centers of power and wealth where conventional success is measured
    - The image of dancing at midnight despite anxiety suggests the paradox of compelled joy or restlessness in the face of life's uncertainties
